HEADWORD: hooch
<hw>hooch</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>an illicitly distilled
(and usually inferior) alcoholic liquor.</def> <mark>[slang]</mark>
<wns>[wns=1]</wns>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> hootch.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Military Slang)</fld> <def>A living quarters;</def>
<specif>especially:</specif> <def>a thatched hut in Southeast Asia, or
any living quarters where a serviceman lives together with a local
woman.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>-hood</ent>⟦br⟧
